    <refsection id="Description_mdaq_adc">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
		This block reads MicroDAQ analog inputs. Block supports different types of MicroDAQ analog inputs, 
		select analog input type by providing 'Converter' parameter accordingly to MicroDAQ hardware configuration.
		In order to read more then one AI channel provide array of channels to read in block 'Channels' parameter. 
		The 'Range', 'Polarity' and 'Mode' ADC block parameters are used to setup converter measurement type. 
		</para>

		<para>This block can be used in host simulation mode and for code generation.</para>

		<para>
		Analog input channel selection in differential mode: 
		<simplelist type="inline">
            <member><para>Channel 1 - AI1(+), AI2(-)</para></member>
			<member><para>Channel 2 - AI1(-), AI2(+)</para></member>
            <member><para>Channel 3 - AI3(+), AI4(-)</para></member>
			<member><para>Channel 4 - AI3(-), AI4(+)</para></member>
            <member><para>Channel 5 - AI5(+), AI6(-)</para></member>
			<member><para>Channel 6 - AI5(-), AI6(+)</para></member>
            <member><para>Channel 7 - AI7(+), AI8(-)</para></member>
			<member><para>Channel 8 - AI7(-), AI8(+)</para></member>
        </simplelist>
		</para>

		<para> Analog inputs input range settings: </para>
		<simplelist type="inline">
            <member><para>0-5V - range: 5, polarity: 1</para></member>
			<member><para>0-10V - range: 10, polarity: 1</para></member>
			<member><para>-/+5V - range: 5, polarity: 2</para></member>
			<member><para>-/+10V - range: 10, polarity: 2</para></member>
        </simplelist>
    </refsection>
	
	<refsection id="InputOutput_mdaq_adc">
        <title>Block Input/Output ports</title>
		<para>
			<simplelist type="inline">
				<member><para>output(1) - raw ADC value (int16)</para></member>
				<member><para>output(2) - ADC value in volts</para></member>
			</simplelist>
		</para>
	</refsection>
